{
  "uid": "v12-4-regex-vars",
  "title": "Grafana 12.4 \u2014 Regex Variable Transforms",
  "description": "12.4 lets you apply a regex to both the variable VALUE and the displayed TEXT. Pick any `handler` below \u2014 the dropdown shows the short name but the query uses the full path.",
  "tags": [
    "grafana-12",
    "v12.4",
    "variables",
    "regex",
    "v12-demo"
  ],
  "schemaVersion": 40,
  "version": 1,
  "editable": true,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-15m",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "timepicker": {},
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "ds_prom",
        "type": "datasource",
        "query": "prometheus",
        "refresh": 1,
        "current": {
          "text": "Prometheus",
          "value": "prom"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "handler_full",
        "label": "Handler (full path)",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "uid": "${ds_prom}",
          "type": "prometheus"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(grafana_http_request_duration_seconds_count, handler)",
          "refId": "StandardVariableQuery"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "multi": false,
        "includeAll": false,
        "hide": 0,
        "regex": "/^(?<value>.+)$/",
        "description": "Captures full path. Displayed short-form via the variable below."
      },
      {
        "name": "handler_short",
        "label": "Handler (display)",
        "type": "query",
        "datasource": {
          "uid": "${ds_prom}",
          "type": "prometheus"
        },
        "query": {
          "query": "label_values(grafana_http_request_duration_seconds_count, handler)",
          "refId": "StandardVariableQuery"
        },
        "refresh": 2,
        "multi": false,
        "includeAll": false,
        "hide": 0,
        "regex": "/^.*\\/(?<text>[^\\/]+)$/",
        "description": "12.4 regex-text transform \u2014 captures only the final path segment for display."
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 10000,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "tags": [
        "demo-guide"
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "content": "<div style=\"padding:1.2rem;background:#1a2a3a;border-left:4px solid #5794f2;border-radius:6px;font-family:system-ui\"><div style=\"font-size:.75rem;letter-spacing:.18em;color:#8aa9d0;margin-bottom:.3rem\">DEMO GUIDE</div><div style=\"font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#fff;margin-bottom:.6rem\">Grafana 12.4 \u2014 Regex Variable Transforms</div><div style=\"display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem\"><div><div style=\"font-weight:600;color:#5794f2;margin-bottom:.2rem\">\ud83c\udfaf What you're looking at</div><div style=\"font-size:.88rem;color:#dfe7f0\">12.4 lets you transform variable values AND display text via regex capture groups. Show short names in the dropdown, query with the full path.</div></div><div><div style=\"font-weight:600;color:#73bf69;margin-bottom:.2rem\">\ud83e\uddea Try this</div><div style=\"font-size:.88rem;color:#dfe7f0\">Pick a handler \u2014 the dropdown shows the short name (last path segment); the query uses the full path.</div></div></div><div style=\"margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.6rem;border-top:1px solid #2d3e54;font-size:.85rem\">\ud83d\udcda <strong style=\"color:#fff\">Learn more</strong>: <a href=\"https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/variables/filter-variables-with-regex/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#ff9830\">Grafana docs</a> \u00b7 <a href=\"https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/whatsnew/whats-new-in-v12-4/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#ff9830\">v12 What's New</a></div></div>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 5,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### Regex variable transforms (12.4)\n\n- **`handler_full`** \u2014 regex `^(?<value>.+)$` keeps the whole path. Used in queries.\n- **`handler_short`** \u2014 regex `^.*/(?<text>[^/]+)$` captures only the last path segment for display.\n\nEach panel below injects both forms so you can see display-vs-value."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "req/s for `${handler_short}` (query value: `${handler_full}`)",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 11,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 12
      },
      "datasource": {
        "uid": "${ds_prom}",
        "type": "prometheus"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "sum by (status_code) (rate(grafana_http_request_duration_seconds_count{handler=\"${handler_full}\"}[$__rate_interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{status_code}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps",
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 15
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right"
        }
      },
      "description": "req/s for `${handler_short}` (query value: `${handler_full}`). Reference: https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/variables/filter-variables-with-regex/"
    }
  ]
}